graph.packing

Class GRASPPackerIntSetNbrhoodFilter2

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.packing.GRASPPackerIntSetNbrhoodFilter2
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IntSetNeighborhoodFilterIntf, NeighborhoodFilterIntf

    class GRASPPackerIntSetNbrhoodFilter2
extends java.lang.Object
implements IntSetNeighborhoodFilterIntf
    implements a filter applicable to local search in GRASP approaches for the 1- or 2-packing problem, as implemented in the popt4jlib.LocalSearch.DLS class. Does not obtain read-lock of the graph to which the nodes belong when accessing nodes' neighbors.

    Title: popt4jlib

    Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

    Copyright: Copyright (c) 2011

    Company:

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Ioannis T. Christou

      • filter

        public java.util.List filter(java.lang.Integer x,
                             java.util.Set arg,
                             java.util.HashMap params)
                      throws LocalSearchException
        provide a List<IntSet> of sets of two integers; in each such set, one of the integers is x, and the other is an integer y in arg which represents the id of a node ny whose immediate neighbors intersect the set of neighbors of x at distance 1 or 2 as specified in the constructor of this object. Essentially, returns a list of sets of pairs of nodes <x,y> for each y in arg, that happens to be at distance 2 or 3 from x, depending on the value of the k-packing problem that is being solved.
        Specified by:
        filter in interface IntSetNeighborhoodFilterIntf
        Parameters:
        x - // Integer
        arg - Set // IntSet values in arg ≤ to the value of x are ignored
        params - HashMap must contain a key-value pair <"dls.graph", Graph g> unless this object was constructed with the 2-arg constructor
        Returns:
        List // ArrayList<IntSet>
        Throws:
        LocalSearchException - if any params are incorrectly set
